<plot>Department store employees Mary Dakin (Anne Nagel) and Bob Spencer (Weldon Heyburn) are married, with Bob not knowing Mary is the granddaughter of millionaire mattress-king Miles Cannon (Harry Davenport.) Mary is content to live on Bob's salary but Bob loses his job and takes Mary to live with her grandfather and then finds out she is heir to a fortune. Bob, furious because Mary deceived him, is determined to make it on his own and goes into business with Crane (John St.Polis), a competitor of Cannon. Eventually, Cannon, Crane and Bob decide to merge, and when Mary announces she is to have a child (the 1938 term for being pregnant), the Spencer family's future is assured.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?474638</url></doc>
